assets_tag.COLUMN_COMMENT: The ID/Tag that the asset carries marked onto it

assetsAssignmentsStatus_id.COLUMN_COMMENT:
0 = None applicable
10 = Pending pick
20 = Picked
30 = Prepping
40 = Tested
50 = Packed
60 = Dispatched
70 = Awaiting Check-in
80 = Case opened
90 = Unpacked
100 = Tested
110 = Stored

instances_emailHeader.COLUMN_COMMENT: A 1200x600 image to be the header on their emails

modulesSteps_locked.COLUMN_COMMENT: When set this is a like system level step that can't be edited

payments_type.COLUMN_COMMENT:
1 = Payment Recieved
2 = Sales item
3 = SubHire item
4 = Staff cost

positions_rank.COLUMN_COMMENT: Rank of the position - so that the most senior position for a user is shown as their "main one". 0 is the most senior

s3files_original_name.COLUMN_COMMENT: What was this file originally called when it was uploaded? For things like file attachments

s3files_meta_size.COLUMN_COMMENT: Size of the file in bytes

s3files_meta_type.COLUMN_COMMENT:
0 = undefined
Rest are set out in corehead

s3files_meta_subType.COLUMN_COMMENT: Depends what it is - each module that uses the file handler will be setting this for themselves

s3files_meta_deleteOn.COLUMN_COMMENT: Delete this file on this set date (basically if you hit delete we will kill it after say 30 days)

s3files_meta_physicallyStored.COLUMN_COMMENT: If we have the file it's 1 - if we deleted it it's 0 but the "deleteOn" is set. If we lost it it's 0 with a null "delete on"

positions_id.COLUMN_COMMENT: Can be null if you like - as long as you set the relevant other fields

userPositions_extraPermissions.COLUMN_COMMENT: Allow a few extra permissions to be added just for this user for that exact permissions term

users_notes.COLUMN_COMMENT: Internal Notes - Not visible to user

users_selectedInstanceIDLast.COLUMN_COMMENT: What is the instance ID they most recently selected? This will be the one we use next time they login
